trend_summary: Across the series, forested tracts slowly give way to patchy cropland and scattered dwellings. A new diagonal highway and several feeder roads appear, stimulating ribbon development but no true town centers. Small clearings enlarge into contiguous fields, while southern woodlots thin. Overall character stays sparsely built and overwhelmingly rural.
notable_changes: Construction of a southwest-to-northeast highway and added feeder roads.
Incremental expansion of cropland, especially in the central and southern sectors.
Reduction of continuous forest cover, replaced by pasture and clearings.
Emergence of small housing clusters along new road intersections.
